peopleAlsoAsk.question: What is the history of the Hoosier flour cabinet?
peopleAlsoAsk.snippet: The cabinet got its name because most of them were made in Indiana. The first Hoosier cabinets appeared in 1898, created by a furniture company called Sellers, in New Castle, Indiana. Popularity of the cabinet grew up until the late 1940's when the records for the cabinets became scarce.

peopleAlsoAsk.question: How to tell the brand of a Hoosier cabinet?
peopleAlsoAsk.snippet: If you're trying to determine if a Hoosier cabinet is genuine, you'll want to look for original components like the flour sifter or those charming roll-top tambour doors. Labels from manufacturers such as Hoosier Manufacturing Co., Sellers, or McDougall are good indicators of authenticity.

peopleAlsoAsk.question: What is the history of McDougall Hoosier cabinets?
peopleAlsoAsk.snippet: McDougall was one of the early manufacturers of a Hoosier cabinet. An advertisement from 1919 identified the McDougall as "the first kitchen cabinet". George McDougall began the McDougall Company in Indianapolis, Indiana, sometime after the Civil War. The company's products were pie safes and kitchen tables.
